{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CPE2MSkg31nF6f5s9eG7JH","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/user-service/output/internal/userservice/store/concurrency.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3acc485c-508a-49bc-82da-fefbb47be33b","uuid":"e4448144-1f52-4d09-89d8-ddad7abac9e5","timestamp":"2026-04-05T08:16:21.844Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/user-service/output/internal/userservice/store/concurrency.md","content":"# concurrency\n\nPurpose: Documents the locking strategy for the Store type, explaining which operations\nacquire read vs. write locks and why.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## Locking Strategy\n\n`Store` embeds a `sync.RWMutex`. The rule is simple: any operation that only reads the\nmap uses a read lock; any operation that modifies the map uses a full write lock.\n\n| Method   | Lock type | Reason |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| `Get`    | `RLock` / `RUnlock` | Read-only; multiple goroutines may read concurrently |\n| `Create` | `Lock` / `Unlock`   | Inserts a new key — map mutation |\n| `Update` | `Lock` / `Unlock`   | Overwrites an existing key — map mutation |\n| `Delete` | `Lock` / `Unlock`   | Removes a key — map mutation |\n\n## Invariants\n\n- The internal map is never `nil` after `New()` returns.\n- `Create` always returns a `User` whose `ID` is a freshly generated UUID; it never\n  returns a zero-value `User`.\n- `Get`, `Update`, and `Delete` signal absence via the boolean second return value /\n  boolean return value — they never panic on a missing key.\n- Locks are always released via `defer` immediately after acquisition to prevent\n  lock leaks on early returns.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PhvahQzhKbEigNtdACj2s8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<response>\n  <outcome>ARCHITECT_DESIGN_READY</outcome>\n  <handoff>Implement package `store` at `internal/userservice/store`. Define a `User` struct (`ID`, `Name`, `Email` strings) and a `Store` struct holding a `map[string]User` plus a `sync.RWMutex`. Provide `New() *Store`, `Create(name, email string) User` (generates a crypto/rand UUID v4, inserts, returns full User), `Get(id string) (User, bool)` (RLock), `Update(id, name, email string) (User, bool)` (Lock; false if missing), `Delete(id string) bool` (Lock; false if missing). UUID generation: fill 16 bytes from crypto/rand, set byte 6 high nibble to 0x40 (version 4) and byte 8 high two bits to 0x80 (variant), format as xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx. No external dependencies. Tests must cover Create returns a populated User with non-empty UUID; Get hit/miss; Update hit/miss (miss must not mutate); Delete hit/miss; concurrent goroutines do not race (run with -race).</handoff>\n  <documents_written>true</documents_written>\n  <design>\n## Design\n\n**Language:** Go, stdlib only (`sync`, `crypto/rand`, `fmt`).\n\n**Package path:** `internal/userservice/store`\n\n**Files to produce:**\n- `store.go` — all types and methods\n- `store_test.go` — table-driven + concurrency tests\n\n**User struct:**\n```go\ntype User struct {\n    ID    string\n    Name  string\n    Email string\n}\n```\n\n**Store struct:**\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    mu      sync.RWMutex\n    records map[string]User\n}\n\nfunc New() *Store {\n    return &Store{records: make(map[string]User)}\n}\n```\n\n**UUID generation (no external deps):**\n```go\nfunc newUUID() string {\n    var b [16]byte\n    _, _ = io.ReadFull(rand.Reader, b[:])\n    b[6] = (b[6] & 0x0f) | 0x40 // version 4\n    b[8] = (b[8] & 0x3f) | 0x80 // variant 10\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%08x-%04x-%04x-%04x-%012x\",\n        b[0:4], b[4:6], b[6:8], b[8:10], b[10:16])\n}\n```\n\n**Method contracts:**\n- `Create`: Lock → generate UUID → store → Unlock → return User\n- `Get`: RLock → lookup → RUnlock → return (User, found)\n- `Update`: Lock → lookup; if missing return (User{}, false); overwrite → Unlock → return (updated User, true)\n- `Delete`: Lock → lookup; if missing return false; delete → Unlock → return true\n\nAll locks released via `defer` immediately after acquisition.\n\n**Constraints:**\n- No third-party packages; only `sync`, `crypto/rand`, `io`, `fmt`.\n- The map is always initialised by `New()` — no nil-map panics possible.\n  </design>\n  <acceptance_criteria>\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. `Create(\"Alice\", \"alice@example.com\")` returns a `User` with non-empty `ID`, `Name == \"Alice\"`, `Email == \"alice@example.com\"`.\n2. Two successive `Create` calls return `User` values with distinct `ID` fields.\n3. `Get` on an ID returned by `Create` returns the same `User` and `true`.\n4. `Get` on an unknown ID returns the zero `User` and `false`.\n5. `Update` on an existing ID returns a `User` with the new name and email, and `true`; the updated values are visible on subsequent `Get`.\n6. `Update` on an unknown ID returns the zero `User` and `false`; the store is unmodified.\n7. `Delete` on an existing ID returns `true`; a subsequent `Get` for that ID returns `false`.\n8. `Delete` on an unknown ID returns `false`.\n9. Running the test binary with `-race` reports no data races when 50 goroutines concurrently call `Create`, `Get`, `Update`, and `Delete`.\n  </acceptance_criteria>\n  <test_command>cd /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/user-service/output && go test -race ./internal/userservice/store/...</test_command>\n</response>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":516,"cache_read_input_tokens":22289,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_